{"talk":{"id":64774,"name":"Menno Schilthuizen: How animals and plants are evolving in cities","description":"In cities, evolution occurs constantly, as countless plants, animals and insects adapt to human-made habitats in spectacular ways. Evolutionary biologist Menno Schilthuizen calls on peculiar beings such as fast food-loving mice and self-cooling snails to illustrate the ever-transforming wonders of urban wildlife -- and explains how you can observe this phenomenon in real-time, thanks to a global network of enthusiastic citizen scientists.","slug":"menno_schilthuizen_how_animals_and_plants_are_evolving_in_cities","recorded_at":"2019-05-04 00:00:00","published_at":"2020-08-24 15:22:29","updated_at":"2020-12-18 11:19:46","viewed_count":0,"emailed_count":0,"event":{"id":649,"name":"TEDxRoma"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/6940021372231cd26bba87a0b038ee4125ec1f10_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/6940021372231cd26bba87a0b038ee4125ec1f10_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/6940021372231cd26bba87a0b038ee4125ec1f10_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"2400x1800","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/6940021372231cd26bba87a0b038ee4125ec1f10_2400x1800.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/2f0200097d19b34be634de5bd506e138b581b142_2880x1620.jpg","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/MennoSchilthuizen_2019X-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":6000468,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/MennoSchilthuizen_2019X-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":16608046,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/MennoSchilthuizen_2019X-320k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":29458037,"mime_type":"vi